children.name: The parallel twin powering the KTM 890 DUKE R engine has been worked into a fire-breathing, highperformance midweight titan. It’s a engineered to suit the aspirations of the most demanding street and track warriors. With its reduced piston weight, increased bore and stroke, higher compression and raised RPM limit, the KTM 890 DUKE R churns out an impressive 121 hp and 99 Nm. A 20per cent increase in rotating mass of the crankshaft has dramatically improved low-end and mid-range rpm, resulting in more responsive riding behavior and delivering a smoother engine at constant speed. This, alongside a lightweight exhaust system, cements the KTM 890 DUKE R on the top rung of the middleweight fight.
